com.vector.cfg.model.access

Interface IDeletedObjectsInfo


  • @PublishedApi(value=ADDITIONS_ALLOWED)
 @ThreadSafe
public interface IDeletedObjectsInfo

    IDeletedObjectsInfo

    IDeletedObjectsInfo objects are provided by the (internal) project service IDeletedObjectsAccessProvider. This service is required because access to content of deleted objects is not possible after deletion. All get-method calls will throw an exception.

    The IDeletedObjectsInfo is an API which provides some basic information about already deleted objects. It is intended to store some characteristics of model objects at least to identify them after deletion.

    Provided information

    The stored information about the deleted object covers:

    • getShortname() returns the shortname of the object
    • getAutosarPath() returns the AUTOSAR path of the object
    • getDefinition() returns the definition of a parameter or container
    • getParentInfo() returns an info object for the parent of the deleted object

    Clients

    The IDeletedObjectsInfo are required for example by validation rules which must be able to validate a model change. These rules must be able to get the context of the object deletion to validate the remaining objects.

    Validation rules can use the interface IRuleEvent to get the deleted info object: 

     void onModelEvent(IValidationResultSink results, IValidationEvents validationEvents) {
       final Collection events = validationEvents.getEvents()

     ...
     for (IRuleEvent event : events) {
         IRuleEvent e = (IRuleEvent) event;
         IDeletedObjectsInfo sourceInfo = e.getSourceInfo();
         ...
     }
     ...
 }

    Lifetime of deleted objects info

    The related provider (internal) service IDeletedObjectsAccessProvider guarantees that these values are available as follows:
    • If the specified object exists, it returns the related model info object
    • If the specified object has been deleted within a currently running transaction (UOW) or the last committed transaction, it returns the related model info object
    • As soon as a new UOW has been started, it cannot be guaranteed anymore that the related info object is still available. If not null will be returned

      Returns true if the related object has been deleted and false else.

      • getDefinition

        @PublishedMethod
DefRef getDefinition()
        The return value of this method depend on the type of the object returned by getMDFObject().
        • For instances of MIHasDefinition, this method never returns null but the returned DefRef object can be DefRef.INVALID_DEFREF if the object doesn't have a valid definition
        • For all other types this method returns null since these objects can never have a definition
        Returns:
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if this object is not valid anymore
